The article discusses how President Trump and his administration are committed to making America safe by implementing evidence-based measures to improve mental health, prevent crime, and keep violent behavior out of schools and communities. Congress has included provisions in the recent government funding legislation to expand mental health programs, giving $700 million to the Department of Education for Student Support and Academic Enrichment grants. These grants allow states to use the money for counseling and mental health service programs. Congress has also passed the STOP School Violence Act and the Fix NICS Act, which provide grants for violence prevention training and enhance background checks to keep firearms out of the wrong hands. The article emphasizes that the administration will continue to work towards ensuring the safety of children in every school and community.